/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  UNIQUAC parameters for ethanol(1)/water(2).

  Pure-component structural constants r (van der Waals volume) and q (surface
  area):
      ethanol  r = 2.1055   q = 1.9720
      water    r = 0.9200   q = 1.4000
  Primary source: Abrams & Prausnitz, AIChE J. 21 (1975) 116; tabulated in
  Poling, Prausnitz & O'Connell, "The Properties of Gases and Liquids", 5th
  ed., Table 8-... (UNIQUAC r,q).

  Binary interaction energies in the temperature form tau_ij = exp(-a_ij / T),
  with a_ij = (u_ij - u_jj)/R in KELVIN.  Here a_ij = (Delta u_ij)/R from the
  interaction energies Delta u_12 = -42.6 cal/mol, Delta u_21 = 442.1 cal/mol
  (R = 1.98720 cal/mol/K), i.e.
      a_12 (ethanol->water) = -21.44 K
      a_21 (water->ethanol) = 222.47 K

  PROVENANCE (honest -- see CLAUDE.md, "cite the PRIMARY source per value"):
  these energies were FITTED here to reproduce the measured infinite-dilution
  activity coefficients of the ethanol(1)-water(2) binary,
      gamma_inf(ethanol in water) ~ 4-8 ,  gamma_inf(water in ethanol) ~ 2-3.5
  (the well-known strongly-non-ideal range; e.g. the VLE compilation in
  Gmehling & Onken, DECHEMA Chemistry Data Series Vol. I/1a).  This set yields
  gamma_inf(eth) ~ 7.7 and gamma_inf(water) ~ 2.75 at ~351 K and the correct
  minimum-boiling azeotrope -- a SANE, cross-checked VLE, not an arbitrary
  aggregator number.  Refit against your own measured set before trusting it
  quantitatively.
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

components       ( ethanol  water );

activityModel
{
    model        UNIQUAC;

    rq
    {
        ethanol  { r 2.1055;  q 1.9720; }
        water    { r 0.9200;  q 1.4000; }
    }

    pairs
    (
        {
            i          ethanol;
            j          water;
            a_ij       -21.44;      // K   (tau_12 = exp(-a_12/T);  Delta u_12 = -42.6 cal/mol)
            a_ji       222.47;      // K   (tau_21 = exp(-a_21/T);  Delta u_21 = 442.1 cal/mol)
        }
    );
}

equationOfState  { model  idealGas; }
